dropped 2 percent to 945.7 at the end of trading in Prague, its
biggest slump since Feb. 10.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of  Austria  fell 4.9 percent
to 402.5 koruna, its lowest close since Jan. 20. Lenders were
among the biggest stock decliners worldwide and commodities fell
after the U.S. Federal Reserve signaled it may refrain from more
monetary stimulus.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, slumped 2.9 percent to 129.1 koruna, its lowest
this year. Benchmark European  coal  derivatives retreated 0.8
